.tmp.driveupload/

# =============================================================================
# Codex harness-state runtime breadcrumbs (added 2026-04-27 S317)
# =============================================================================
# Per-session payload, stderr, and trigger-input from .codex/agent-red-hooks/
# hook dispatch. Replaceable on every Stop/SessionStart hook invocation.
.codex/agent-red-hooks/last-session-start.json
.codex/agent-red-hooks/last-session-start.err
.codex/agent-red-hooks/last-wrapup-trigger-input.json

# =============================================================================
# Mutable session-lifecycle guard JSONs (added 2026-04-27 S317)
# =============================================================================
# Cross-session armed-state with timestamps and counters. Treated as runtime
# until harness-state-authority-migration-2026-04-27 thread VERIFIED. Then
# the in-root paths become canonical and may be tracked.
.codex/agent-red-hooks/session-lifecycle-guard.json
applications/Agent_Red/harness-state/*/session-lifecycle-guard.json

# =============================================================================
# Hardlink aliases of canonical harness-state files (added 2026-04-28 S319)
# =============================================================================
# Per bridge/session-hygiene-gitignore-extensions-2026-04-28-002.md (GO):
# These .codex/agent-red-hooks/ paths are hardlink aliases of canonical-home
# tracked files at applications/Agent_Red/harness-state/codex/. Tracking both
# would create dual-canonical confusion. The canonical home is tracked; the
# aliases are silently ignored. Distinct from runtime breadcrumbs (above) and
# mutable lifecycle-guard JSONs (above) — these are stable static content.
.codex/agent-red-hooks/operating-role.md
.codex/agent-red-hooks/session-startup-preferences.json

# =============================================================================
# Phase 1 isolation: post-relocation runtime paths (added 2026-04-29 S320)
# =============================================================================
# Per bridge/gtkb-isolation-phase1-implementation-2026-04-28-007.md GO at -008:
# .codex/gtkb-hooks/ replaces the now-deleted .codex/agent-red-hooks/. Durable
# launchers and dispatchers ARE tracked; runtime breadcrumbs and lifecycle-guard
# files generated by tracked dispatcher source are ignored. Enumerated from
# tracked dispatcher source per -007 §2.6.2 methodology.
.codex/gtkb-hooks/last-session-start.json
.codex/gtkb-hooks/last-session-start.err
.codex/gtkb-hooks/last-session-stop.json
.codex/gtkb-hooks/last-session-stop.err
.codex/gtkb-hooks/last-wrapup-trigger-input.json
.codex/gtkb-hooks/last-wrapup-trigger.json
.codex/gtkb-hooks/last-wrapup-trigger.err
.codex/gtkb-hooks/session-lifecycle-guard.json

# Root-level harness-state replaces applications/Agent_Red/harness-state/.
# Durable operating-role.md and session-startup-preferences.json ARE tracked;
# the per-harness session-lifecycle-guard.json is runtime-mutable.
harness-state/*/session-lifecycle-guard.json

# =============================================================================
# MEMORY.md trim backups (added 2026-04-28 S319)
# =============================================================================
# Per bridge/session-hygiene-gitignore-extensions-2026-04-28-002.md (GO) and
# bridge/gtkb-startup-enhancements-p1-006.md (S309 P1 origin): one-time
# point-in-time backups before MEMORY.md trim operations. Pre-trim state
# is already preserved in git history at the commit before the trim;
# tracking the backup file is redundant and creates noise on future trims.
memory/MEMORY.md.backup-*

# =============================================================================
# Smart-poller runtime state (added 2026-04-29 S321)
# =============================================================================
# Per bridge/session-hygiene-drift-triage-s321-2026-04-29-003.md §2.4 +
# Codex NO-GO -002 "Additional Notes": .gtkb-state/ is the smart-poller's
# runtime state directory written every 15s by the active scheduled task
# (audit.jsonl, checkpoint.json, notifications/, poller-runs/). Pure runtime
# state — never a tracking candidate. Missed in S320 activation work.
.gtkb-state/

# =============================================================================
# Formal-artifact-approval session-state packets (added 2026-04-29 S321)
# =============================================================================
# Per bridge/session-hygiene-drift-triage-s321-2026-04-29-003.md §2.3 +
# acting-prime-builder.md "Formal Artifact Approval And Audit Principle":
# these JSON packets are governance approval evidence consumed by the
# formal-artifact-approval-gate.py PreToolUse hook. After harvest into the
# Deliberation Archive (groundtruth.db), the JSON is redundant. Tracking
# would duplicate KB state and create per-session diff noise.
.groundtruth/formal-artifact-approvals/
